Silent Warrior:<br><br>
Okay, so you slipped off and took the Tom Dier, &quot;How to be a nice guy course..&quot; without telling me, Art and Cookie (of course Cookie would eat the crayons and Art probably couldn't pass the dress code...soooo-o-o...you are forgiven!<br><br>
&quot;Wankanl yanka, wa'sicun, wanyaka tuwena icun'sni.&quot; comes to my mind.  It means, in a roundabout way.. A strange mystery to have to deal with...A messenger who behaves and acts in a manner that is referred to as &quot;look, no one acts in this manner,&quot; inferring that it is not good for the people...nor is it &quot;normal.&quot;<br><br>
&quot;IT&quot; has served a purpose here for some.  While many veterans limp through life, hamstrung by an unspecified anger, they have no real target for venting their anger.  That anger turned inward = depression = immobilization = PTSD..etc.  The available targets are too grandiose ..politicians..hippies...Military....Congress... draft boards.. etc.  Anger weakens judgement.  Many angry veterans turn anger on themselves rather than taking a chance on &quot;throwing the baby out with the dirty bath water!&quot;  Sadly, for many, they have already done that too many times!<br><br>
&quot;IT&quot; comes along and presents a tangible target!<br><br>
This is good and bad..Good because a population of emotionally wounded can accquire or repair anger transfer and defusing skills...Bad because the target is a human... a highly disfunctional one at that!<br><br>
Graduating to a higher level..we may focus on ourselves.  Pick targets such as greed...egotism...pain and death... the greatness of lost friends.  Perhaps we can heal our wounds with love for one another rather than hatred for the anatagonist.<br><br>
Jesus came to heal the sick.. something for Christians to remember.  Mustang Two Four aka Tatekohomni Wambli aka P-38 Man aka Deer Slayer aka SIR!..came to heal Cook Barela aka Sparrow Droppings ..something for Marines to remember!!!<br><br>
I am glad, Slobbering Warrior, Brother of Choice, Wingman of Choice, that you are able to feel... even if it is anger or pain.  You've gone a long way in your life.. it is now time for you, me and the other BOCs to come a long way.<br><br>
Tried to kill a fawn this morning..  missed.. the bullet richoceted off a rock, a hard pumpkin and two trees before killing it's robust father.  Oh well, meat's meat.  Having some ground into sausage in case Pizza Breath or others come to visit. (Black Powder Guns are gross.. P-38's do a neater job!)<br><br>
My very best to you..the very best Brothers!<br><br>
P.S.  Had to rent a low boy to haul him into the check station!
